   "source": [
    "### Exploring CDC Places 2021 dataset\n",
    "CDC PLACES: Local Data for Better Health\n",
    "Available at: https://www.cdc.gov/places/\n",
    "County-level data download: https://data.cdc.gov/500-Cities-Places/PLACES-Local-Data-for-Better-Health-County/pqpp-u99h/about_data\n",
    "\n",
    "CDC PLACES is a collaboration between the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC), the Robert Wood Johnson Foundation, and the CDC Foundation. The dataset provides model-based health estimates for counties, places, census tracts, and ZIP Code Tabulation Areas across the United States. The estimates are generated using Behavioral Risk Factor Surveillance System (BRFSS) survey data combined with Census demographic information through small-area estimation techniques.\n",
    "\n",
    "This project uses the county-level 2021 release."
   ]
