   "source": [
    "This preliminary state-level mismatch table identifies states where average poor mental health prevalence is high relative to the number of SAMHSA mental health facilities. West Virginia has the highest mismatch score in this draft measure, followed by Tennessee, Arkansas, Alabama, and Louisiana.\n",
    "\n",
    "This is still a rough infrastructure measure because it uses total facility counts rather than county-level accessibility or facility capacity. "
   ]
  },
